BATMAN (1966)

5: A Horse of Another Color    10/12/1967
Penguin schemes to make a bundle for Lola and himself by disguising the glue factory reject as Parasol and the real Parasol under the moniker of Bumber shoot; that way, everyone will bet on the paste Parasol, while The Penguin will make a killing from a wager on the true horse, which is an unmistakeable long shot!
  Guest star: Burgess Meredith (The Penguin) , Ethel Merman (Lola Lasagne), Horace McMahon (Glu Gluten), Lewis Charles (Armband), Herbert Anderson (Racing Secretary), Constance Davis (Myrtle), Allen Emerson (Photographer), Joe Brooks (Visor)

6. The Unkindest Tut of All   10/19/1967  
The Nabob of the Nile returns to Tut-ness after being hit on the head with a brick during a love-in. "Retired," he sets himself up in a tent on 6th and Albert streets as a public crime predictor.
  Guest star: Victor Buono (King Tut) , James Ramsey (TV Announcer), Cathleen Cordell (Librarian), Patti Gilbert (Shirley), James Gammon (Osris), Larry Duran (Nubis)

7. Louie the Lilac   10/26/1967  
Commissioner Gordon plans a "flower-in" at Gotham City City Park but is disappointed to learn that there are no flowers available. Meanwhile, the dastardly Louie The Lilac plans to "take over" the minds of Gotham City&#039;s flower children ? and he begins by kidnapping one of their leaders, Princess Primrose (having placed her under the power of his nefarious Lilac Spray),  
  Guest star: Richard Bakalyan (Arbutus) , Schuyler Aubrey (Princess Primrose/Thelma Jones), Jimmy Boyd (Dogwood), Karl Lukas (Acacia), Lisa Seagram (Lila), Milton Berle (Louie the Lilac)

8. The Ogg and I (1)    11/2/1967  
Incognito as a deliveryman, Egghead kidnaps Commissioner Gordon from his office at Police HQ with the aid of Olga and a getaway baloon!
  Guest star: Vincent Price (Egghead), Anne Baxter (Olga, Queen Of The Cossacks), James O&#039;Hara (Policeman), Pat Becker (Technician) , Alfred Dennis (Omar Orloff), Alan Hale Jr. (Gilligan), Violet Carlson (Old Lady), Billy Corcoran (Boy Scout), James Lanphier (Indian Man), Mary Benoit (Petula), Jon Lormer (Professor Dactyl), Donald Elson (Tender)

9. How to Hatch a Dinosaur (2)    11/9/1967 
Egghead, Queen Olga and The Cossacks raid The Gotham City Radium Center and rob 2 lbs. of radium. Later, as Barbara Gordon visits her friend Professor Dactyl at The Gotham Museum, Egghead and Olga grab a giant fossilized 40 million year-old Neosaurus egg, unbeknownst to Barbara or Dactyl!  
  Guest star: Vincent Price (Egghead), Anne Baxter (Olga, Queen Of The Cossacks), James O&#039;Hara (Policeman), Pat Becker (Technician) , Alfred Dennis (Omar Orloff), Alan Hale Jr. (Gilligan), Violet Carlson (Old Lady), Billy Corcoran (Boy Scout), James Lanphier (Indian Man), Mary Benoit (Petula), Jon Lormer (Professor Dactyl), Donald Elson (Tender)
